Their father has just died, and Frank, the oldest, has flown down from Chicago to see the angry newlywed Ned and the ex-con Johnny. Over the course of one long day the Ballard boys destroy everything and everyone in their way — drinking, cursing, and revealing family secrets that might just tear them apart forever. Playwright Samuel Brett Williams explores family, love, and mortality in a dark comedy that culminates in a race that you will never forget.',production:['59e59 Theatre','Gilded Balloon (Edinburgh, Scotland)','Red Door Studios','Clifton Performance Theatre','Camisade Theatre Company','Elephant Theatre Company'],development:["National Theatre Institute at the Eugene O' Neill Theatre Center","Studio 42"],info:'',videos:['https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34']},{id:4,title:'The Revival',cover:"placeholder.png",photos:[1,2,3],duration:'Full Length',synopsis:'A desperate young man wanders into town looking for food and shelter. A progressive pastor tries to open the minds of his Old Testament congregation. A born again, recovering alcoholic fights for his church. A pastor’s wife looks to her gay husband for salvation. All of this comes to a scorching climax, resulting in an old time Revival the small Arkansas town will never forget. Playwright Samuel Brett Williams explores faith in the Deep South in a drama that asks how far you’re willing to go for the things you believe in.',production:['Project Y Theatre Company'],development:['The Kennedy Center','P73 Productions','Yale University','Ars Nova Play Group'],info:'',videos:['https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34']},{id:5,title:'The Woodpecker',cover:"placeholder.png",photos:[1,2,3],duration:'Full Length',synopsis:'It’s Jimmy’s last day before going to war, he’s addicted to glue, his mom is seeing visions in the sweet potato casserole, and his wheelchair-bound dad can kick his ass. He turns to God for answers, and finds…an Ivory-Billed Woodpecker. Playwright Samuel Brett Williams explores family, faith, and freedom in a dark comedy that blurs the lines between black and white and right and wrong.',production:['Cherry Lane Theatre','XIII Pocket','Mutineer Playwrights Conference'],development:["Eugene O'Neill National Playwrights Conference"],info:'',videos:['https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34']},{id:6,title:'Revelation',cover:"placeholder.png",photos:[1,2,3],duration:'Full Length',synopsis:'Brandon’s Southern Baptist father always taught him to be prepared for the Rapture. For Christmas, his mother even sent him a Rapture Kit: bottled water, canned food, a Bible, and a mouthpiece (for the gnashing of teeth). Rebecca is a pre med student who was raised as an atheist. All of a sudden people begin disappearing, the Hudson River turns to blood, and the entire state of Ohio comes down with a bad case of the boils. Brandon grabs Rebecca and tries to make it from New York City to Arkadelphia, Arkansas in hopes of finding the New Jerusalem. Playwright Samuel Brett Williams explores faith, love, and the American landscape in a pitch black comedy about the End Days.',production:['Untethered Theatre Company','Shelterbelt Theatre','Elephant Theatre Company'],development:["Boise Contemporary Theatre","Lark Play Development Center","BRIDGE Playwrights Laboratory","Playwrights Theatre of New Jersey","Ars Nova Out Loud Series (Workshop) (Directed by Evan Cabnet)","Partial Comfort Productions (Workshop)"],info:'Commisioned by the National New Play Network',videos:['https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34']},{id:7,title:'Missed Connections',cover:"placeholder.png",photos:[1,2,3],duration:'10 Minutes',synopsis:'Two people on a first date try to muster up the courage necessary to NOT give love a chance.',production:['The Neighborhood Playhouse','Great Plains Theatre Conference','Actors Theatre of Ithaca','Ars Nova'],development:[""],info:'',videos:['https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34']},{id:8,title:'Arkadelphia',cover:"placeholder.png",photos:[1,2,3],duration:'One Act',synopsis:'Bobby returns to his hometown of Arkadelphia, Arkansas after a semester of college in Manhattan. Seeking refuge in two childhood friends, he ends up exposing a secret the small, religious town would rather keep buried. Playwright Samuel Brett Williams challenges the ideals of the South, the North, and everywhere in between.',production:['Rutgers University'],development:["Neighborhood Playhouse","Lark Play Development Center"],info:'',videos:['https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34']},{id:9,title:'Trash Bag Tourist',cover:"placeholder.png",photos:[1,2,3],duration:'One Act',synopsis:'The Trash Bag Tourist portrays the relationship between ancient, manipulative Dorothy and her rundown, rodeo clown daughter Molly. They are both stuck in a wheel-less trailer in Arkadelphia, Arkansas when a Katrina victim (Chuck) shows up, threatening their already hostile relationship. Chuck has dreams of getting a FEMA trailer and becoming a professional wrestler, but Dorothy has other plans. Playwright Samuel Brett Williams finds love in the lowest of circumstances, all the while exploring family, race, and the American Dream.',production:['New Orleans Theatre Experiment'],development:["Project Y Theatre Company","Neighborhood Playhouse"],info:'',videos:['https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9VF8AXvOg34']}];
